    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Windows</title>
        <para>The standard passenger windows are an aluminum extruded window assembly. The windows are equipped with a
            positive latch drop down type upper window section. Slide latch mechanisms are located at the upper corners
            of each window assembly to lock the window in the desired position. The window assemblies are completely
            removable for serviceability, from the bus interior.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700463" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G4700463.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 63. Standard Passenger Windows</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. TOP WINDOW LOCKING LATCH</callout1>
                <callout1>2. WINDOW POST COVER PLATE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. EMERGENCY WINDOW LOCKING LATCH</callout1>
                <callout1>4. EMERGENCY WINDOW LOCK LATCH</callout1>
                <callout1>5. EMERGENCY WINDOW LOWER GLASS PANEL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Passenger windows are sealed thermal glass panels that are easily serviced if damaged.</para>
        <figure id="f4700464" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G4700464.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 64. Emergency Exit Push Out Windows</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. WINDOW LATCHES</callout1>
                <callout1>2. UPPER WINDOW PANE (WINDOW AND FRAME SLIDES UP AND DOWN)</callout1>
                <callout1>3. WINDOW TRIM COVER PLATES</callout1>
                <callout1>4. STATIONARY WINDOW PANE (LOWER)</callout1>
                <callout1>5. EMERGENCY WINDOW RELEASE LATCH</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>The bus body is equipped with emergency exit windows and doors. Opening an emergency window or door will
            activate an alarm or buzzer (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700465">Fig. 65, Item 4</hotlnk>) at the driver's position when the key is in the on or
            accessory position. Depending on the local requirements the emergency window will unlatch and push out and
            is either vertically or horizontally hinged.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700465" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G4700465.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 65. Emergency Window Open - Relay Switch</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1, WINDOW SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>2. EMERGENCY WINDOW EXIT LATCH</callout1>
                <callout1>3. EMERGENCY WINDOW EXIT CLIP</callout1>
                <callout1>4. EMERGENCY WINDOW AJAR WARNING SWITCH</callout1>
                <callout1>5. LOWER WINDOW SILL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
